                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n                              <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                                        <date>Novr. 19. 1845</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Revd. Dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Enclosed are $3.00 for this<lb/> year's Occident\n                                        from <persName>Mr. B. Lichtenstein</persName>,\n                                                  <placeName>Buffalo</placeName>.<lb/> I should feel\n                                        obliged if you would send me the <date>Sep<lb/>tember</date>\n                                        No. <del>which</del> as I have lost it.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Dr. Lilienthal</persName> late of\n                                                  <placeName>St. Petersburg</placeName> has\n                                        ar<lb/>rived. It is very probable that You may secure\n                                        his<lb/> aid for your paper. I have seen him last night<lb/>\n                                        he told me that he intended to reduce the obser<lb/>vations\n                                        he has made concerning our co-religionists<lb/> during his\n                                        stay in <placeName>Russia</placeName> to writing\n                                        communicate<lb/> them to the Zeitung des Juden [?]. I\n                                        remarked to him<lb/> that it would be very desirable for the\n                                        English<lb/> Jews generally if his essays on the\n                                        subject<lb/> would appear simultaneously in the English<lb/>\n                                        Press that you would certainly publish his\n                                        com<lb/>munications with pleasure. The condition of<lb/> our\n                                        brethren in <placeName>Russia</placeName>, according to his\n                                        accounts,<lb/> are wretched beyond our conception.\n                                        Hitherto<lb/> they have at least enjoyed the liberty of\n                                        following<lb/> the religion of our fathers, but this boon\n                                        will<lb/> in all probability very soon been denied\n                                        them.<lb/> To renounce their religion or die, will be\n                                        the<lb/> only alternative left them. A sad cala<lb/>mity for\n                                        2 millions of our brethren.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Dr. L.</persName> tenders you, through\n                                        me, his kind regards</p>\n                              "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hq3sq7b/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
